<p>I am passing a string such as "abc\n" to a program that stores in a string in a buffer, and then printing what was passed in.</p>  <p>Like this:</p>  <pre><code>int main(int argc, char **argv) {    char buffer[5];    strncpy(buffer, argv[1], 5);    printf("%s", buffer);     return 0; } </code></pre>  <p>My argument is then this: <code>"abc\n"</code></p>  <p>But then the string that prints out is this: <code>abc\n</code></p>  <p>How come it doesn't add a new line after abc?</p>